whereas.text:
Whereas tax incentives are an important impetus for
			 individuals to save for retirement and for employers to offer plans under our
			 voluntary system;

Whereas more than 70 percent of American workers making
			 between $30,000 and $50,000 a year contribute to their own retirement when
			 covered by a retirement plan at work;

Whereas under current law, if business owners and managers
			 sponsor a retirement plan, they also must cover and provide benefits to
			 lower-income and middle-income employees;
